-- German Credit Lines Less Tapped as Cash Flow Used, BdB Says
-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 2012-05-31T08:25:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-31/german-credit-lines-less-tapped-as-cash-flow-used-bdb-says.html
Germany ’s banks’ credit lines to the
country’s companies remain increasingly untapped, as the healthy
state of the German economy means firms rely on  cash flow  rather
than credit facilities, the BdB Association of German banks said
in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
